# Demonstrate guessing impact
cat("\n=== GUESSING TÆSÄ°RÄ°NÄ°N DEMONSTRASÄ°YASI ===\n")
## 
## === GUESSING TÆSÄ°RÄ°NÄ°N DEMONSTRASÄ°YASI ===
demonstrate_guessing_impact <- function() {
  # Scenario: 4-option multiple choice test
  theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.2)
  
  # Item parameters
  discrimination <- 1.5
  difficulty <- 0
  
  # Without guessing (2PL)
  prob_no_guessing <- prob_2pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty)
  
  # With 25% guessing (3PL)
  guessing_param <- 0.25
  prob_with_guessing <- prob_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, guessing_param)
  
  # Plot comparison
  plot(theta_range, prob_no_guessing, type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
       main = "Guessing TÉ™siri: 2PL vs 3PL ICC",
       xlab = "Theta (Î¸)", ylab = "P(X = 1 | Î¸)",
       ylim = c(0, 1), xlim = c(-4, 4))
  
  lines(theta_range, prob_with_guessing, lwd = 3, col = "red")
  abline(h = c(0, 0.25, 0.5), lty = c(1, 2, 2), col = c("black", "red", "gray"))
  
  legend("right", c("2PL (No guessing)", "3PL (25% guessing)", "Chance level"), 
         col = c("blue", "red", "red"), lwd = c(3, 3, 1), lty = c(1, 1, 2))
  
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Key insights
  cat("Key Observations:\n")
  cat("1. 3PL never drops below chance level (c = 0.25)\n")
  cat("2. Very low ability persons still have 25% success chance\n")
  cat("3. Effective range of discrimination reduced\n") 
  cat("4. Steepest part of curve shifted upward\n\n")
  
  # Numerical comparison
  very_low_theta <- -3
  prob_2pl_low <- prob_2pl(very_low_theta, discrimination, difficulty)
  prob_3pl_low <- prob_3pl(very_low_theta, discrimination, difficulty, guessing_param)
  
  cat("At Î¸ = -3 (very low ability):\n")
  cat("2PL probability:", round(prob_2pl_low, 3), "\n")
  cat("3PL probability:", round(prob_3pl_low, 3), "\n")
  cat("Difference:", round(prob_3pl_low - prob_2pl_low, 3), "\n")
  
  return(list(
    theta = theta_range,
    prob_2pl = prob_no_guessing,
    prob_3pl = prob_with_guessing
  ))
}

guessing_demo <- demonstrate_guessing_impact()

## Key Observations:
## 1. 3PL never drops below chance level (c = 0.25)
## 2. Very low ability persons still have 25% success chance
## 3. Effective range of discrimination reduced
## 4. Steepest part of curve shifted upward
##

# Demonstrate realistic c parameter effects
cat("\n=== MÃœXTÆLÄ°F c PARAMETER DÆYÆRLÆRÄ°NÄ°N TÆSÄ°RÄ° ===\n")
## 
## === MÃœXTÆLÄ°F c PARAMETER DÆYÆRLÆRÄ°NÄ°N TÆSÄ°RÄ° ===
demonstrate_c_parameter_effects <- function() {
  theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
  discrimination <- 1.2
  difficulty <- 0
  
  # Different c values
  c_values <- c(0, 0.10, 0.20, 0.25, 0.33)
  c_labels <- c("No guessing", "10% guess", "20% guess", "25% guess (4-opt)", "33% guess (3-opt)")
  
  plot(theta_range, prob_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, 0),
       type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
       main = "MÃ¼xtÉ™lif c Parametr DÉ™yÉ™rlÉ™rinin ICC-yÉ™ TÉ™siri",
       xlab = "Theta (Î¸)", ylab = "P(X = 1 | Î¸)",
       ylim = c(0, 1))
  
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple")
  for(i in 1:length(c_values)) {
    prob <- prob_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, c_values[i])
    lines(theta_range, prob, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
    
    # Add horizontal line for c value
    if(c_values[i] > 0) {
      abline(h = c_values[i], lty = 3, col = colors[i])
    }
  }
  
  legend("right", c_labels, col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.8)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Calculate effective discrimination ranges
  cat("Effective Discrimination Ranges:\n")
  for(i in 1:length(c_values)) {
    effective_range <- 1 - c_values[i]  # Range from c to 1
    cat(sprintf("c = %.2f: Effective range = %.2f (%.0f%% of full range)\n", 
                c_values[i], effective_range, 100 * effective_range))
  }
  
  return(list(theta = theta_range, c_values = c_values))
}

c_effects <- demonstrate_c_parameter_effects()

## Effective Discrimination Ranges:
## c = 0.00: Effective range = 1.00 (100% of full range)
## c = 0.10: Effective range = 0.90 (90% of full range)
## c = 0.20: Effective range = 0.80 (80% of full range)
## c = 0.25: Effective range = 0.75 (75% of full range)
## c = 0.33: Effective range = 0.67 (67% of full range)
cat("\nPraktik Ä°mplikasiyalar:\n")
## 
## Praktik Ä°mplikasiyalar:

  "â€¢ YÃ¼ksÉ™k c â†’ Discrimination azalmasÄ±",
  "â€¢ YÃ¼ksÉ™k c â†’ Information function shift", 
  "â€¢ c = 0.25+ â†’ Measurement precision loss",
  "â€¢ Variable c across items â†’ Complex analysis",
  "â€¢ c estimation â†’ Large sample size requirement",
  "â€¢ High c â†’ Consider test design revision"
)

  cat(implication, "\n")
}

## â€¢ YÃ¼ksÉ™k c â†’ Information function shift

3 3PL Modelinin Riyazi Ä°fadÉ™si

3.1 Fundamental Equations vÉ™ Parameter InterpretasiyasÄ±

cat("=== 3PL MODELÄ°NÄ°N RÄ°YAZÄ° Ä°FADÆSÄ° ===\n\n")
## === 3PL MODELÄ°NÄ°N RÄ°YAZÄ° Ä°FADÆSÄ° ===
cat("1. Æsas 3PL TÉ™nliyi:\n")
## 1. Æsas 3PL TÉ™nliyi:
cat("P(Xáµ¢ = 1 | Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢, cáµ¢) = cáµ¢ + (1 - cáµ¢) Ã— exp[aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)] / (1 + exp[aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)])\n\n")
## P(Xáµ¢ = 1 | Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢, cáµ¢) = cáµ¢ + (1 - cáµ¢) Ã— exp[aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)] / (1 + exp[aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)])
cat("2. Alternatif Form:\n")
## 2. Alternatif Form:
cat("P(Xáµ¢ = 1 | Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢, cáµ¢) = cáµ¢ + (1 - cáµ¢) Ã— Pâ‚‚â‚šâ‚—(Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢)\n\n")
## P(Xáµ¢ = 1 | Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢, cáµ¢) = cáµ¢ + (1 - cáµ¢) Ã— Pâ‚‚â‚šâ‚—(Î¸, aáµ¢, báµ¢)
cat("3. Logit TransformasiyasÄ± (kompleks):\n")
## 3. Logit TransformasiyasÄ± (kompleks):
cat("ln[(P - cáµ¢)/(1 - P)] = aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)\n\n")
## ln[(P - cáµ¢)/(1 - P)] = aáµ¢(Î¸ - báµ¢)
# Parameter detailed explanation
parameter_details_3pl <- data.frame(
  Parameter = c("Î¸ (theta)", "aáµ¢ (alpha)", "báµ¢ (beta)", "cáµ¢ (gamma)", "Xáµ¢"),
  
  Name = c("Person ability", "Item discrimination", "Item difficulty", 
           "Pseudo-guessing", "Item response"),
  
  Range = c("-âˆž to +âˆž", "0 to +âˆž", "-âˆž to +âˆž", "0 to 1", "0 or 1"),
  
  Typical_Values = c("-3 to +3", "0.5 to 3.0", "-3 to +3", "0.0 to 0.35", "0 or 1"),
  
  Interpretation = c("Higher = more able", "Higher = steeper ICC", "Higher = harder item",
                     "Lower asymptote", "1 = correct"),
  
  Estimation_Difficulty = c("Moderate", "Moderate", "Easy", "Hard", "N/A")
)

# Fixed discrimination and difficulty, varying c
theta_example <- 0
disc_example <- 1.5
diff_example <- 0

cat("Î¸ = 0, a = 1.5, b = 0, mÃ¼xtÉ™lif c dÉ™yÉ™rlÉ™ri:\n")
## Î¸ = 0, a = 1.5, b = 0, mÃ¼xtÉ™lif c dÉ™yÉ™rlÉ™ri:
c_values_example <- c(0.00, 0.10, 0.20, 0.25, 0.30)
prob_examples <- sapply(c_values_example, function(c) 
  prob_3pl(theta_example, disc_example, diff_example, c))

example_table <- data.frame(
  c_Parameter = c_values_example,
  Probability = round(prob_examples, 3),
  vs_2PL_Difference = round(prob_examples - prob_2pl(theta_example, disc_example, diff_example), 3),
  Interpretation = c("Same as 2PL", "10% boost", "20% boost", "25% boost (4-opt)", "30% boost")
)

print(example_table)

## 4        0.25       0.625             0.125 25% boost (4-opt)
## 5        0.30       0.650             0.150         30% boost
# Effect at different theta levels
cat("\nMÃ¼xtÉ™lif Î¸ sÉ™viyyÉ™lÉ™rindÉ™ c = 0.25 tÉ™siri:\n")
## 
## MÃ¼xtÉ™lif Î¸ sÉ™viyyÉ™lÉ™rindÉ™ c = 0.25 tÉ™siri:
theta_levels <- c(-3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3)
c_fixed <- 0.25

prob_2pl_levels <- prob_2pl(theta_levels, disc_example, diff_example)
prob_3pl_levels <- prob_3pl(theta_levels, disc_example, diff_example, c_fixed)

theta_effect_table <- data.frame(
  Theta = theta_levels,
  Prob_2PL = round(prob_2pl_levels, 3),
  Prob_3PL = round(prob_3pl_levels, 3),
  Difference = round(prob_3pl_levels - prob_2pl_levels, 3),
  Relative_Impact = round((prob_3pl_levels - prob_2pl_levels) / prob_2pl_levels, 2)
)

print(theta_effect_table)

# Mathematical properties
cat("\n=== 3PL MODELÄ°NÄ°N RÄ°YAZÄ° XÃœSUSÄ°YYÆTLÆRÄ° ===\n")
## 
## === 3PL MODELÄ°NÄ°N RÄ°YAZÄ° XÃœSUSÄ°YYÆTLÆRÄ° ===
mathematical_properties <- data.frame(
  Property = c("Lower Asymptote", "Upper Asymptote", "Inflection Point", 
               "Maximum Slope", "Effective Range", "Symmetry"),
  
  Mathematical_Form = c("lim(Î¸â†’-âˆž) P = c", "lim(Î¸â†’+âˆž) P = 1", "Î¸* â‰  b", 
                        "slope_max = a(1-c)/4", "1-c", "Not logit-symmetric"),
  
  Practical_Meaning = c("Chance level", "Perfect performance", "Steepest point shifted",
                        "Reduced from 2PL", "Compressed scale", "Asymmetric around midpoint"),
  
  Implication = c("Never below c", "Always can reach 1", "Complex targeting",
                  "Less discrimination", "Reduced precision", "Complex interpretation")
)

print(mathematical_properties)
##           Property    Mathematical_Form          Practical_Meaning
## 1  Lower Asymptote      lim(Î¸â†’-âˆž) P = c               Chance level
## 2  Upper Asymptote      lim(Î¸â†’+âˆž) P = 1        Perfect performance
## 3 Inflection Point               Î¸* â‰  b     Steepest point shifted
## 4    Maximum Slope slope_max = a(1-c)/4           Reduced from 2PL
## 5  Effective Range                  1-c           Compressed scale
## 6         Symmetry  Not logit-symmetric Asymmetric around midpoint
##              Implication
## 1          Never below c
## 2     Always can reach 1
## 3      Complex targeting
## 4    Less discrimination
## 5      Reduced precision
## 6 Complex interpretation

4 ICC-nin Asimptotik DavranÄ±ÅŸÄ± vÉ™ Æyri FormalarÄ±

4.1 Lower Asymptote vÉ™ Effective Difficulty

cat("=== ICC-NÄ°N ASÄ°MPTOTÄ°K DAVRANIÅžI ===\n\n")
## === ICC-NÄ°N ASÄ°MPTOTÄ°K DAVRANIÅžI ===
# Comprehensive ICC comparison
demonstrate_asymptotic_behavior <- function() {
  theta_range <- seq(-5, 5, by = 0.05)
  
  # Fixed parameters for comparison
  discrimination <- 1.5
  difficulty <- 0
  
  # Multiple c values
  c_values <- c(0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.25, 0.33)
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple")
  
  plot(theta_range, prob_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, 0),
       type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
       main = "3PL ICC Asimptotik DavranÄ±ÅŸ (a=1.5, b=0)",
       xlab = "Theta (Î¸)", ylab = "P(X = 1 | Î¸)",
       ylim = c(0, 1), xlim = c(-5, 5))
  
  for(i in 1:length(c_values)) {
    prob <- prob_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, c_values[i])
    lines(theta_range, prob, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
    
    # Mark asymptotes
    abline(h = c_values[i], lty = 3, col = colors[i])
    if(c_values[i] > 0) {
      text(-4, c_values[i] + 0.02, paste("c =", c_values[i]), 
           col = colors[i], cex = 0.8)
    }
  }
  
  # Mark important points
  abline(h = c(0, 0.5, 1), lty = c(1, 2, 1), col = "gray")
  abline(v = difficulty, lty = 2, col = "gray")
  
  legend("right", paste("c =", c_values), col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.8)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  return(list(theta = theta_range, c_values = c_values))
}

asymptotic_demo <- demonstrate_asymptotic_behavior()

cat("\n=== EFFECTÄ°VE DÄ°FFÄ°CULTY KONSEPTÄ° ===\n")
## 
## === EFFECTÄ°VE DÄ°FFÄ°CULTY KONSEPTÄ° ===
# Effective difficulty calculation
calculate_effective_difficulty <- function(discrimination, difficulty, guessing) {
  # Theta value where P(theta) = 0.5
  # For 3PL: 0.5 = c + (1-c) * exp(a(Î¸*-b)) / (1 + exp(a(Î¸*-b)))
  # Solving: Î¸* = b + (1/a) * ln((0.5-c)/(1-0.5))
  
  if(guessing >= 0.5) return(NA)  # No solution when c >= 0.5
  
  effective_diff <- difficulty + (1/discrimination) * log((0.5 - guessing)/(1 - 0.5))
  return(effective_diff)
}

cat("Effective Difficulty HesablamasÄ±:\n")

cat("Effective difficulty = b + (1/a) Ã— ln[(0.5-c)/(1-0.5)]\n\n")
## Effective difficulty = b + (1/a) Ã— ln[(0.5-c)/(1-0.5)]

# Slope analysis
cat("\n=== SLOPE ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===\n")
## 
## === SLOPE ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===
# Maximum slope occurs at inflection point, not at b
calculate_max_slope_location <- function(discrimination, difficulty, guessing) {
  # For 3PL, inflection point is at:
  # Î¸* = b + (1/a) * ln[(1-c)/c]
  
  if(guessing <= 0 || guessing >= 1) return(difficulty)
  
  inflection_point <- difficulty + (1/discrimination) * log((1 - guessing)/guessing)
  return(inflection_point)
}

# Examples
slope_analysis_table <- data.frame(
  c_Parameter = c_values_eff,
  b_True = rep(difficulty_ex, length(c_values_eff)),
  Inflection_Point = round(sapply(c_values_eff, function(c) 
    calculate_max_slope_location(discrimination_ex, difficulty_ex, c)), 3),
  Max_Slope = round(discrimination_ex * (1 - c_values_eff) / 4, 3),
  Slope_vs_2PL = round(((discrimination_ex * (1 - c_values_eff) / 4) / 
                       (discrimination_ex / 4) - 1) * 100, 1)
)

slope_analysis_table$Slope_vs_2PL <- paste0(slope_analysis_table$Slope_vs_2PL, "%")

5 3PL Information Functions

5.1 Information Degradation vÉ™ Precision Loss

cat("=== 3PL INFORMATION FUNCTÄ°ONS ===\n\n")
## === 3PL INFORMATION FUNCTÄ°ONS ===
cat("3PL Information Function Formula:\n")
## 3PL Information Function Formula:
cat("I(Î¸) = [aÂ²(P-c)Â²(1-P)] / [P(1-c)Â²]\n\n")
## I(Î¸) = [aÂ²(P-c)Â²(1-P)] / [P(1-c)Â²]
# Information function comparison
demonstrate_3pl_information <- function() {
  theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
  discrimination <- 1.5
  difficulty <- 0
  
  # Different c values
  c_values <- c(0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.25, 0.33)
  colors <- c("blue", "green", "orange", "red", "purple")
  
  # Calculate information for each c
  plot(theta_range, info_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, 0),
       type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
       main = "3PL Information Functions (a=1.5, b=0)",
       xlab = "Theta (Î¸)", ylab = "Information I(Î¸)",
       ylim = c(0, 0.6))
  
  for(i in 1:length(c_values)) {
    info <- info_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, c_values[i])
    lines(theta_range, info, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
  }
  
  legend("topright", paste("c =", c_values), col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.8)
  grid(TRUE)
  
  # Calculate peak information
  peak_info <- numeric(length(c_values))
  peak_location <- numeric(length(c_values))
  
  for(i in 1:length(c_values)) {
    info <- info_3pl(theta_range, discrimination, difficulty, c_values[i])
    max_idx <- which.max(info)
    peak_info[i] <- info[max_idx]
    peak_location[i] <- theta_range[max_idx]
  }
  
  return(list(
    c_values = c_values,
    peak_info = peak_info,
    peak_location = peak_location
  ))
}

cat("\n=== TEST INFORMATION COMPARISON ===\n")
## 
## === TEST INFORMATION COMPARISON ===
# Simulate a test with mixed c parameters
set.seed(2025)
n_items <- 10

# Mixed item parameters
discriminations <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.2)
difficulties <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)

# Scenario 1: No guessing (2PL)
c_params_2pl <- rep(0, n_items)

# Scenario 2: Moderate guessing (3PL)  
c_params_3pl <- runif(n_items, 0.05, 0.25)

# Calculate test information
theta_seq <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.2)
test_info_2pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))
test_info_3pl <- numeric(length(theta_seq))

for(i in 1:length(theta_seq)) {
  theta <- theta_seq[i]
  
  # 2PL test information
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    p <- prob_2pl(theta, discriminations[j], difficulties[j])
    test_info_2pl[i] <- test_info_2pl[i] + discriminations[j]^2 * p * (1-p)
  }
  
  # 3PL test information  
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    info <- info_3pl(theta, discriminations[j], difficulties[j], c_params_3pl[j])
    test_info_3pl[i] <- test_info_3pl[i] + info
  }
}

# Plot test information comparison
plot(theta_seq, test_info_2pl, type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
     main = "Test Information: 2PL vs 3PL (10 items)",
     xlab = "Theta (Î¸)", ylab = "Test Information",
     ylim = c(0, max(test_info_2pl, test_info_3pl) * 1.1))

lines(theta_seq, test_info_3pl, lwd = 3, col = "red")

legend("topright", c("2PL (no guessing)", "3PL (with guessing)"), 
       col = c("blue", "red"), lwd = 3)

grid(TRUE)

# Test-level summary
max_info_2pl <- max(test_info_2pl)
max_info_3pl <- max(test_info_3pl)
optimal_theta_2pl <- theta_seq[which.max(test_info_2pl)]
optimal_theta_3pl <- theta_seq[which.max(test_info_3pl)]

cat("Test-Level Information Comparison:\n")
## Test-Level Information Comparison:
cat("2PL Maximum Information:", round(max_info_2pl, 2), "at Î¸ =", round(optimal_theta_2pl, 1), "\n")
## 2PL Maximum Information: 3.57 at Î¸ = 0.2
cat("3PL Maximum Information:", round(max_info_3pl, 2), "at Î¸ =", round(optimal_theta_3pl, 1), "\n")
## 3PL Maximum Information: 1.85 at Î¸ = 0.4
cat("Information Loss:", round((1 - max_info_3pl/max_info_2pl) * 100, 1), "%\n")
## Information Loss: 48.2 %
cat("SE at optimal (2PL):", round(1/sqrt(max_info_2pl), 3), "\n")
## SE at optimal (2PL): 0.529
cat("SE at optimal (3PL):", round(1/sqrt(max_info_3pl), 3), "\n")
## SE at optimal (3PL): 0.735

# Practical model selection simulation
cat("\n=== PRAKTÄ°K MODEL SEÃ‡Ä°MÄ° SÄ°MULYASÄ°YASI ===\n")
## 
## === PRAKTÄ°K MODEL SEÃ‡Ä°MÄ° SÄ°MULYASÄ°YASI ===
simulate_model_selection <- function() {
  set.seed(67890)
  
  n_persons <- 800
  n_items <- 20
  
  # Scenario 1: True 3PL data (with guessing)
  theta_true <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  
  # Item parameters
  disc_true <- runif(n_items, 0.7, 2.3)
  diff_true <- seq(-2.5, 2.5, length.out = n_items)
  guess_true <- runif(n_items, 0.05, 0.30)  # Realistic guessing range
  
  # Generate 3PL data
  data_3pl <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_3pl(theta_true[i], disc_true[j], diff_true[j], guess_true[j])
      data_3pl[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data_3pl) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  
  return(list(
    data = data_3pl,
    true_params = list(
      theta = theta_true,
      discrimination = disc_true,
      difficulty = diff_true,
      guessing = guess_true
    )
  ))
}

simulation_data <- simulate_model_selection()

cat("Model SeÃ§imi SimulyasiyasÄ±:\n")

    "-", round(max(simulation_data$true_params$guessing), 3), "\n\n")

# Basic descriptive statistics

## Mean score: 11.7 / 20

## Item difficulty range: 0.212 - 0.975
# Check for lower asymptote evidence
very_low_scorers <- total_scores <= quantile(total_scores, 0.1)
low_ability_performance <- mean(item_means[simulation_data$data[very_low_scorers, ]])

7 R-dÉ™ 3PL Analizi

7.1 ltm vÉ™ mirt PaketlÉ™ri ilÉ™ 3PL Implementation

cat("=== R-DÆ 3PL ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===\n\n")
## === R-DÆ 3PL ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===
# ltm paketi ilÉ™ 3PL analizi
perform_3pl_ltm_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== LTM 3PL ANALÄ°ZÄ°:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(ltm, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("ltm paketi mÃ¶vcud deyil.\n")
    return(NULL)
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    cat("Model fitting: 1PL, 2PL, 3PL...\n")
    
    # Fit different models
    model_1pl <- rasch(data, constraint = cbind(1:ncol(data), 1))
    model_2pl <- ltm(data ~ z1)
    model_3pl <- tpm(data)  # Three Parameter Model
    
    cat("Models fitted successfully.\n\n")
    
    # Model comparison
    cat("=== MODEL MÃœQAYÄ°SÆ ===\n")
    
    # Extract fit statistics
    aic_1pl <- AIC(model_1pl)
    aic_2pl <- AIC(model_2pl)
    aic_3pl <- AIC(model_3pl)
    
    bic_1pl <- BIC(model_1pl)
    bic_2pl <- BIC(model_2pl)
    bic_3pl <- BIC(model_3pl)
    
    loglik_1pl <- logLik(model_1pl)
    loglik_2pl <- logLik(model_2pl)
    loglik_3pl <- logLik(model_3pl)
    
    fit_comparison <- data.frame(
      Model = c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL"),
      LogLik = round(c(as.numeric(loglik_1pl), as.numeric(loglik_2pl), as.numeric(loglik_3pl)), 2),
      AIC = round(c(aic_1pl, aic_2pl, aic_3pl), 2),
      BIC = round(c(bic_1pl, bic_2pl, bic_3pl), 2),
      Parameters = c(ncol(data), 2*ncol(data), 3*ncol(data))
    )
    
    print(fit_comparison)
    
    # Best model by AIC and BIC
    best_aic <- fit_comparison$Model[which.min(fit_comparison$AIC)]
    best_bic <- fit_comparison$Model[which.min(fit_comparison$BIC)]
    
    cat("\nBest model by AIC:", best_aic, "\n")
    cat("Best model by BIC:", best_bic, "\n")
    
    # Likelihood ratio tests
    cat("\n=== LIKELIHOOD RATIO TESTS ===\n")
    
    tryCatch({
      lr_2pl_vs_1pl <- anova(model_1pl, model_2pl)
      cat("2PL vs 1PL:\n")
      print(lr_2pl_vs_1pl)
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("2PL vs 1PL test failed\n")
    })
    
    tryCatch({
      lr_3pl_vs_2pl <- anova(model_2pl, model_3pl)
      cat("3PL vs 2PL:\n")
      print(lr_3pl_vs_2pl)
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("3PL vs 2PL test failed\n")
    })
    
    # 3PL parameters
    cat("\n=== 3PL PARAMETRLÆRÄ° ===\n")
    
    params_3pl <- coef(model_3pl)
    
    # Extract parameters (ltm specific format)
    discrimination_3pl <- params_3pl[, "Dscrmn"]
    difficulty_3pl <- params_3pl[, "Dffclt"]
    guessing_3pl <- params_3pl[, "Gussng"]
    
    item_params_3pl <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:length(discrimination_3pl),
      Discrimination = round(discrimination_3pl, 3),
      Difficulty = round(difficulty_3pl, 3),
      Guessing = round(guessing_3pl, 3),
      Quality_Disc = ifelse(discrimination_3pl < 0.5, "Poor",
                           ifelse(discrimination_3pl < 1.0, "Fair",
                                 ifelse(discrimination_3pl < 1.5, "Good", "Excellent"))),
      Guessing_Level = ifelse(guessing_3pl < 0.05, "Minimal",
                             ifelse(guessing_3pl < 0.15, "Low",
                                   ifelse(guessing_3pl < 0.25, "Moderate", "High")))
    )
    
    print(head(item_params_3pl, 10))
    
    # Summary statistics
    cat("\n3PL Parameter Summary:\n")
    cat("Discrimination: Mean =", round(mean(discrimination_3pl), 3), 
        ", SD =", round(sd(discrimination_3pl), 3), "\n")
    cat("Difficulty: Mean =", round(mean(difficulty_3pl), 3), 
        ", SD =", round(sd(difficulty_3pl), 3), "\n")
    cat("Guessing: Mean =", round(mean(guessing_3pl), 3), 
        ", SD =", round(sd(guessing_3pl), 3), "\n")
    cat("Guessing range:", round(min(guessing_3pl), 3), "-", round(max(guessing_3pl), 3), "\n")
    
    # High guessing items
    high_guessing <- sum(guessing_3pl > 0.25)
    cat("Items with high guessing (c > 0.25):", high_guessing, "/", length(guessing_3pl), "\n")
    
    return(list(
      model_1pl = model_1pl,
      model_2pl = model_2pl,
      model_3pl = model_3pl,
      fit_comparison = fit_comparison,
      item_params = item_params_3pl,
      best_model_aic = best_aic,
      best_model_bic = best_bic
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("LTM 3PL analysis xÉ™tasÄ±:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# mirt paketi ilÉ™ 3PL analizi
perform_3pl_mirt_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("\n=== MIRT 3PL ANALÄ°ZÄ°:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(mirt, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("mirt paketi mÃ¶vcud deyil.\n")
    return(NULL)
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    cat("MIRT model fitting: 1PL, 2PL, 3PL...\n")
    
    # Fit models
    model_1pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "Rasch", verbose = FALSE)
    model_2pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
    model_3pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "3PL", verbose = FALSE)
    
    cat("MIRT models fitted successfully.\n\n")
    
    # Model comparison
    cat("=== MIRT MODEL MÃœQAYÄ°SÆ ===\n")
    
    fit_1pl_mirt <- extract.mirt(model_1pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_2pl_mirt <- extract.mirt(model_2pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_3pl_mirt <- extract.mirt(model_3pl_mirt, "fit")
    
    mirt_fit_comparison <- data.frame(
      Model = c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL"),
      LogLik = round(c(fit_1pl_mirt["logLik"], fit_2pl_mirt["logLik"], fit_3pl_mirt["logLik"]), 2),
      AIC = round(c(fit_1pl_mirt["AIC"], fit_2pl_mirt["AIC"], fit_3pl_mirt["AIC"]), 2),
      BIC = round(c(fit_1pl_mirt["BIC"], fit_2pl_mirt["BIC"], fit_3pl_mirt["BIC"]), 2)
    )
    
    print(mirt_fit_comparison)
    
    # Model comparison tests
    cat("\n=== MIRT MODEL COMPARISON TESTS ===\n")
    
    tryCatch({
      comparison_3pl_2pl <- anova(model_2pl_mirt, model_3pl_mirt)
      cat("3PL vs 2PL Comparison:\n")
      print(comparison_3pl_2pl)
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Model comparison test failed:", e$message, "\n")
    })
    
    # 3PL parameters
    cat("\n=== MIRT 3PL PARAMETRLÆRÄ° ===\n")
    
    params_3pl_mirt <- coef(model_3pl_mirt, simplify = TRUE)
    item_params_mirt <- params_3pl_mirt$items
    
    mirt_params_table <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:nrow(item_params_mirt),
      Discrimination = round(item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
      Difficulty = round(-item_params_mirt[, "d"] / item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
      Guessing = round(item_params_mirt[, "g"], 3),
      SE_Disc = round(params_3pl_mirt$SEitems[, "a1"], 3),
      SE_Guess = round(params_3pl_mirt$SEitems[, "g"], 3)
    )
    
    print(head(mirt_params_table, 10))
    
    # Parameter diagnostics
    cat("\nMIRT Parameter Diagnostics:\n")
    
    # Check for boundary estimates
    boundary_g <- sum(mirt_params_table$Guessing < 0.001 | mirt_params_table$Guessing > 0.49)
    high_se_g <- sum(mirt_params_table$SE_Guess > 0.1, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    cat("Boundary guessing estimates (â‰¤0.001 or â‰¥0.49):", boundary_g, "\n")
    cat("High SE guessing estimates (>0.1):", high_se_g, "\n")
    
    if(boundary_g > 0 || high_se_g > 0) {
      cat("WARNING: Estimation issues detected. Consider 2PL model.\n")
    }
    
    return(list(
      model_3pl = model_3pl_mirt,
      fit_comparison = mirt_fit_comparison,
      item_params = mirt_params_table,
      estimation_issues = list(boundary_g = boundary_g, high_se_g = high_se_g)
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("MIRT 3PL analysis xÉ™tasÄ±:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# Parameter recovery assessment
if(!is.null(ltm_3pl_result) && !is.null(ltm_3pl_result$item_params)) {
  cat("\n=== PARAMETER RECOVERY ASSESSMENT ===\n")
  
  # Compare estimated vs true parameters (first 10 items)
  n_compare <- min(10, nrow(ltm_3pl_result$item_params))
  
  recovery_table <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:n_compare,
    True_Disc = round(simulation_data$true_params$discrimination[1:n_compare], 3),
    Est_Disc = round(ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Discrimination[1:n_compare], 3),
    True_Diff = round(simulation_data$true_params$difficulty[1:n_compare], 3),
    Est_Diff = round(ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Difficulty[1:n_compare], 3),
    True_Guess = round(simulation_data$true_params$guessing[1:n_compare], 3),
    Est_Guess = round(ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Guessing[1:n_compare], 3)
  )
  
  print(recovery_table)
  
  # Correlations
  cor_disc <- cor(simulation_data$true_params$discrimination[1:n_compare], 
                  ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Discrimination[1:n_compare])
  cor_diff <- cor(simulation_data$true_params$difficulty[1:n_compare], 
                  ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Difficulty[1:n_compare])
  cor_guess <- cor(simulation_data$true_params$guessing[1:n_compare], 
                   ltm_3pl_result$item_params$Guessing[1:n_compare])
  
  cat("\nParameter Recovery Correlations:\n")
  cat("Discrimination:", round(cor_disc, 3), "\n")
  cat("Difficulty:", round(cor_diff, 3), "\n")
  cat("Guessing:", round(cor_guess, 3), "\n")
  
  # Overall recovery quality
  if(all(c(cor_disc, cor_diff, cor_guess) > 0.8, na.rm = TRUE)) {
    recovery_quality <- "Excellent"
  } else if(all(c(cor_disc, cor_diff, cor_guess) > 0.6, na.rm = TRUE)) {
    recovery_quality <- "Good"
  } else {
    recovery_quality <- "Poor"
  }
  
  cat("Overall parameter recovery:", recovery_quality, "\n")
}

## 5    Extreme difficulties         Sparse data           More data
## 6         Non-convergence   Model too complex      Simplify model
##                 Prevention
## 1 Check for guessing first
## 2             Large sample
## 3            Item analysis
## 4 Multiple starting values
## 5          Adequate sample
## 6           Start with 2PL
# Demonstrate estimation sensitivity
cat("\n=== ESTÄ°MATÄ°ON SENSÄ°TÄ°VÄ°TY DEMONSTRASÄ°YA ===\n")
## 
## === ESTÄ°MATÄ°ON SENSÄ°TÄ°VÄ°TY DEMONSTRASÄ°YA ===
demonstrate_estimation_sensitivity <- function() {
  # Use different sample sizes from true 3PL data
  true_data <- simulation_data$data
  true_params <- simulation_data$true_params
  
  sample_sizes <- c(200, 400, 600, 800, 1200)
  
  sensitivity_results <- data.frame(
    Sample_Size = integer(),
    Convergence = character(),
    Mean_c_Est = numeric(),
    SD_c_Est = numeric(),
    Boundary_Items = integer(),
    Recovery_Quality = character()
  )
  
  for(n in sample_sizes) {
    cat("Testing sample size:", n, "\n")
    
    # Subsample data
    indices <- sample(1:nrow(true_data), min(n, nrow(true_data)))
    sub_data <- true_data[indices, ]
    
    # Simple estimation assessment
    total_scores <- rowSums(sub_data, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    # Check for evidence of guessing using simple heuristic
    very_low_scorers <- total_scores <= quantile(total_scores, 0.1)
    if(length(very_low_scorers) > 10) {
      low_ability_performance <- colMeans(sub_data[very_low_scorers, ], na.rm = TRUE)
      estimated_c <- pmax(0, low_ability_performance - 0.05)  # Simple proxy
    } else {
      estimated_c <- rep(0.1, ncol(sub_data))  # Default
    }
    
    # Assess estimation quality
    convergence <- ifelse(n >= 800, "Likely", ifelse(n >= 400, "Possible", "Unlikely"))
    boundary_items <- sum(estimated_c < 0.02 | estimated_c > 0.45)
    
    if(n >= 800) {
      recovery_quality <- "Good"
    } else if(n >= 400) {
      recovery_quality <- "Fair"
    } else {
      recovery_quality <- "Poor"
    }
    
    sensitivity_results <- rbind(sensitivity_results, data.frame(
      Sample_Size = n,
      Convergence = convergence,
      Mean_c_Est = round(mean(estimated_c), 3),
      SD_c_Est = round(sd(estimated_c), 3),
      Boundary_Items = boundary_items,
      Recovery_Quality = recovery_quality
    ))
  }
  
  print(sensitivity_results)
  
  return(sensitivity_results)
}

# Run sensitivity analysis
sensitivity_results <- demonstrate_estimation_sensitivity()

cat("\n=== CASE STUDY: STANDARDIZED TEST ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===\n")
## 
## === CASE STUDY: STANDARDIZED TEST ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===
# Simulate a realistic standardized test scenario
simulate_standardized_test <- function() {
  set.seed(98765)
  
  # Test specifications
  n_examinees <- 1500  # Large operational sample
  n_items <- 40        # Typical test length
  
  # Realistic parameter distributions
  # Discrimination: Good quality items
  discrimination <- rgamma(n_items, shape = 2.5, rate = 1.8)  # Mean â‰ˆ 1.4
  
  # Difficulty: Well-targeted test
  difficulty <- rnorm(n_items, mean = 0, sd = 1.2)
  
  # Guessing: Realistic for 4-option MC
  # Most items 15-25%, some higher, few lower
  guessing <- rbeta(n_items, shape1 = 2, shape2 = 6) * 0.3 + 0.05
  
  # Examinee abilities: Realistic distribution
  theta <- rnorm(n_examinees, mean = 0.2, sd = 1.1)
  
  # Generate test data
  test_data <- matrix(NA, n_examinees, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_examinees) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_3pl(theta[i], discrimination[j], difficulty[j], guessing[j])
      test_data[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(test_data) <- paste0("Q", 1:n_items)
  
  return(list(
    data = test_data,
    true_params = list(
      theta = theta,
      discrimination = discrimination,
      difficulty = difficulty,
      guessing = guessing
    ),
    specifications = list(
      n_examinees = n_examinees,
      n_items = n_items,
      format = "4-option multiple choice",
      context = "Standardized admission test"
    )
  ))
}

# Generate case study data
case_study <- simulate_standardized_test()
